==English==

===Etymology===
German ''[[strafe]]'' (in "''Gott strafe England''", "God punish England", 1914).

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪf|-eɪf]]

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|strafes|strafing|strafed}}

# to attack (ground targets) with automatic gunfire from a low-flying aircraft.
# in computer games, to [[sidestep]]. Originally applied to an attack method of sidestepping while shooting, the term  has broadened to mean moving sideways in any fashion.

===Noun===
'''strafe'''

# an attack of machine-gun or cannon fire from a low-flying aircraft.

